00:19:20,726 --> 00:19:23,362
Told if I cooperated,

253
00:19:23,394 --> 00:19:25,564
no further charges would
be made against me.

254
00:19:26,865 --> 00:19:28,865
They would give me money.

255
00:19:30,868 --> 00:19:32,868
And, you declined?

256
00:19:33,838 --> 00:19:36,307
As you see.

257
00:19:36,340 --> 00:19:38,710
Of course! I cannot
endorse that.

258
00:19:38,743 --> 00:19:40,679
I feel duty-bound to urge you,

259
00:19:40,711 --> 00:19:42,814
to cooperate with the U.S.
government.

260
00:19:42,847 --> 00:19:44,249
I said no.

261
00:19:44,282 --> 00:19:47,486
Perhaps you could relay to your
friends at the CIA that I meant it.

262
00:19:47,519 --> 00:19:49,520
No, no, no. I am not.

263
00:19:49,555 --> 00:19:51,555
I do not work for the agency.

264
00:19:53,392 --> 00:19:55,460
I do not work for
the government.

265
00:19:55,493 --> 00:19:58,730
I am here to offer my services
as your legal counsel.

266
00:19:58,763 --> 00:20:01,599
If you accept them as such,

267
00:20:02,768 --> 00:20:04,768
I work for you.

268
00:20:04,903 --> 00:20:06,903
If I accept you.

269
00:20:13,478 --> 00:20:15,478
Are you good on what you do?

270
00:20:16,914 --> 00:20:19,483
Yeah. Yeah, I am very good.

271
00:20:21,920 --> 00:20:25,590
Have you represented
many accused spies?

272
00:20:28,527 --> 00:20:30,527
No, not yet.

273
00:20:31,762 --> 00:20:34,398
This will be the
first for both.

274
00:20:37,935 --> 00:20:39,935
Yes.

275
00:20:41,640 --> 00:20:43,407
All right!

276
00:20:43,442 --> 00:20:45,442
<i>"All right"? You accept.</i>

277
00:20:47,511 --> 00:20:48,846
Yes, all right!

278
00:20:48,880 --> 00:20:51,383
Good, okay.

279
00:20:51,415 --> 00:20:52,550
Let us start here.

280
00:20:52,584 --> 00:20:53,719
If you are firm in
your resolve it,

281
00:20:53,751 --> 00:20:55,354
not to cooperate with the U.S.
government...

282
00:20:55,386 --> 00:20:56,488
I am.

283
00:20:56,520 --> 00:20:57,923
Yeah.

284
00:20:57,955 --> 00:20:59,790
<i>Then do not talk to anybody
else about your case.</i>

285
00:20:59,825 --> 00:21:01,526
Inside of government
or outside.

286
00:21:01,559 --> 00:21:04,663
Except to me, to the
extent that you trust me.

287
00:21:04,695 --> 00:21:06,698
I have a mandate to serve you.
Nobody else does.

288
00:21:06,731 --> 00:21:08,500
Frankly, everybody else
has an interest...

289
00:21:08,532 --> 00:21:10,532
in sending you to
the electric chair.

290
00:21:10,669 --> 00:21:12,669
All right!

291
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:17,440
You do not seem alarmed.

292
00:21:21,980 --> 00:21:23,980
Would it help?

293
00:21:33,858 --> 00:21:37,929
I would like
materials to draw.

294
00:21:37,962 --> 00:21:39,962
<i>That is not possible.</i>

295
00:21:40,464 --> 00:21:42,401
A pencil, a piece of paper.

296
00:21:42,433 --> 00:21:44,433
Cigarettes.

297
00:21:45,971 --> 00:21:47,971
Please?

298
00:21:55,012 --> 00:21:57,816
Mr. Donovan, you
is a man like me,

299
00:21:57,848 --> 00:22:00,419
doing the same for
your country.

300
00:22:01,519 --> 00:22:03,888
If they were caught...

301
00:22:03,922 --> 00:22:06,825
I am sure that you wish
them treated well.

302
00:22:11,496 --> 00:22:12,763
<i>What is your name?</i>

303
00:22:12,798 --> 00:22:14,798
Francis Gary Powers.

304
00:22:16,634 --> 00:22:18,470
Rank, service?

305
00:22:18,502 --> 00:22:20,705
First Lieutenant, United
States Air Force.

306
00:22:22,773 --> 00:22:24,476
Do you have any association?

307
00:22:24,509 --> 00:22:26,510
With the Soviet Union,
Lieutenant Powers.

308
00:22:26,545 --> 00:22:27,746
Are you kidding?

309
00:22:27,778 --> 00:22:28,946
Just answer the
questions, lieutenant.

310
00:22:28,980 --> 00:22:31,549
Yes, no, or as
simply as you can.

311
00:22:31,583 --> 00:22:33,751
Do you have any association
with the Soviet Union?

312
00:22:33,785 --> 00:22:35,785
Hell, no.

313
00:22:37,055 --> 00:22:39,055
Do you know why you are here?

314
00:22:40,625 --> 00:22:42,794
Is that a no?

315
00:22:42,827 --> 00:22:45,029
Yes. I mean...

316
00:22:45,063 --> 00:22:46,932
No. It is just "no."

317
00:22:46,964 --> 00:22:49,500
Yes. I have absolutely
no idea why I am here.

318
00:22:49,534 --> 00:22:50,701
Eyes front, Lieutenant.

319
00:22:50,736 --> 00:22:52,736
Yes, sir.

320
00:23:09,621 --> 00:23:11,621
How would you do
in there, Gary?

321
00:23:12,691 --> 00:23:15,594
Very good. I think. I
got my name right.

322
00:23:15,626 --> 00:23:18,563
You probably outscored
Shin, then.

323
00:23:20,030 --> 00:23:21,465
Who is winning?

324
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:22,733
That would be me.

325
00:23:22,768 --> 00:23:24,702
Well, deal me in.

326
00:23:24,736 --> 00:23:26,938
<i>These are all mine, then.</i>

327
00:23:26,971 --> 00:23:28,971
<i>I told you boys not
to play with him.</i>

328
00:23:55,834 --> 00:23:57,834
Okay, drivers.
Here is the deal.

329
00:23:59,136 --> 00:24:01,006
You selected for a mission.

330
00:24:01,038 --> 00:24:02,574
Which you are not to discuss.

331
00:24:02,606 --> 00:24:04,875
With anyone outside
of this room.

332
00:24:04,910 --> 00:24:06,644
No one.

333
00:24:06,678 --> 00:24:08,712
I do not care who you trust.

334
00:24:08,747 --> 00:24:10,714
Wife, mother, sweetheart.

335
00:24:10,749 --> 00:24:12,717
The good Lord when
you pray at night.

336
00:24:12,750 --> 00:24:14,685
You do not tell any
of them anything.

337
00:24:14,719 --> 00:24:16,719
Of what I am about
to tell you.

338
00:24:19,023 --> 00:24:21,990
Each of drivers has met
certain qualifications.

339
00:24:22,626 --> 00:24:24,829
High-level security clearance.

340
00:24:24,863 --> 00:24:26,631
<i>Exceptional pilot ratings...</i>

341
00:24:26,664 --> 00:24:28,633
<i>in excess of the required
hour's flight time...</i>

342
00:24:28,666 --> 00:24:30,602
<i>in a single-seat aircraft.</i>

343
00:24:30,634 --> 00:24:33,605
We are engaged in a war.

344
00:24:33,637 --> 00:24:35,874
A war does in this moment,
not involve men-at-arms.

345
00:24:35,997 --> 00:24:37,776
It involves information.

346
00:24:37,808 --> 00:24:40,010
You will be collecting
information.

347
00:24:40,045 --> 00:24:42,881
You will be gathering
intelligence about the enemy.

348
00:24:42,913 --> 00:24:46,550
The intelligence you gather
could give us the upper hand...

349
00:24:46,585 --> 00:24:49,990
in a full thermonuclear
exchange with the Soviet Union.

350
00:24:51,155 --> 00:24:53,155
Or it could prevent one.

351
00:24:53,924 --> 00:24:56,126
<i>For public purposes,</i>

352
00:24:56,161 --> 00:24:57,828
as far as your wife or mother.

353
00:24:57,962 --> 00:24:59,830
Or, sweetheart, the good Lord,

354
00:24:59,964 --> 00:25:01,967
your mission does not exist.

355
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:04,836
If it does not exist.
You do not exist.

356
00:25:04,869 --> 00:25:08,272
You cannot be shot down.
You cannot be captured.

357
00:25:14,712 --> 00:25:16,712
You work for the CIA now.

358
00:25:28,960 --> 00:25:32,797
Jim, I heard your person is
speaking with a phony accent.

359
00:25:33,898 --> 00:25:35,901
Does he keep this
up all the time?

360
00:25:35,933 --> 00:25:38,670
Actually, I am sure that
is just the way he talks.

361
00:25:38,702 --> 00:25:40,805
He has the Russian name.
However, a British passport.

362
00:25:40,838 --> 00:25:43,741
I doubt that is genuine.

363
00:25:43,775 --> 00:25:46,044
So, Jim, where are we?
I see here...

364
00:25:46,076 --> 00:25:48,680
Yes. Judge, you see...

365
00:25:48,712 --> 00:25:53,084
I just do not think that three
weeks are going to do it.

366
00:25:53,218 --> 00:25:55,086
We got a massive amount
of evidence, as you know.

367
00:25:55,220 --> 00:25:56,186
Do you want to postpone?

368
00:25:56,221 --> 00:25:57,388
Six weeks.

369
00:25:57,422 --> 00:26:00,892
I mean, there is just myself
and, my associate.

370
00:26:00,925 --> 00:26:02,126
Jim, is this serious?

371
00:26:02,160 --> 00:26:04,160
Sir?

372
00:26:06,230 --> 00:26:07,999
Is this serious?

373
00:26:08,032 --> 00:26:09,667
Yes. Yes, indeed it is.

374
00:26:09,990 --> 00:26:11,102
You can see in the file.

375
00:26:11,135 --> 00:26:13,971
Jim, this man is a Soviet spy.

376
00:26:14,005 --> 00:26:16,674
- Allegedly.
- Come on! Counselor!

377
00:26:18,242 --> 00:26:19,743
Your Honor.

378
00:26:19,978 --> 00:26:21,179
Of course, I salute you.

379
00:26:21,311 --> 00:26:23,748
We all salute you for
taking on a thankless task.

380
00:26:23,882 --> 00:26:25,650
This man has due process.

381
00:26:25,884 --> 00:26:27,884
Let us not kid each other.

382
00:26:28,153 --> 00:26:30,989
<i>He will receive a
capable defense.</i>

383
00:26:31,021 --> 00:26:34,726
And, God willing.
He will be convicted.

384
00:26:34,759 --> 00:26:36,126
Come on! Counselor.

385
00:26:36,161 --> 00:26:37,695
Let us not play
games with this.

386
00:26:37,729 --> 00:26:39,830
Not in my courtroom.

387
00:26:39,864 --> 00:26:41,865
We have a date.

388
00:26:41,900 --> 00:26:43,900
And, we are going to trial.

389
00:26:52,911 --> 00:26:54,878
<i>Taxi!</i>

390
00:26:54,913 --> 00:26:56,681
Taxi!

391
00:26:56,714 --> 00:26:59,683
I see your light on!
Son of a bitch!

392
00:27:01,051 --> 00:27:03,755
You cannot wait to get
back to Manhattan.

393
00:27:03,788 --> 00:27:05,788
His light was on, right?

394
00:27:06,124 --> 00:27:08,124
Son of a bitch!

395
00:27:54,972 --> 00:27:56,807
Against their
level of comfort.

396
00:27:56,840 --> 00:27:57,909
The statute has not changed.

397
00:27:57,942 --> 00:27:59,344
Excuse me, Sir.

398
00:27:59,376 --> 00:28:01,376
Pardon me. Sorry.

399
00:28:32,376 --> 00:28:34,376
Mr. Donovan?

400
00:28:37,181 --> 00:28:39,181
What?

401
00:28:42,385 --> 00:28:44,385
What?

402
00:28:55,299 --> 00:28:57,268
CIA.

403
00:28:57,301 --> 00:28:58,301
Yeah.

404
00:28:59,203 --> 00:29:01,203
I just wanted to chat.

405
00:29:04,843 --> 00:29:06,176
How is the case going?

406
00:29:06,211 --> 00:29:08,980
The case is going great,
could not be better.

407
00:29:10,981 --> 00:29:12,981
Has your person talked?

408
00:29:16,453 --> 00:29:19,089
Excuse me.

409
00:29:19,124 --> 00:29:21,859
You met him. Has he talked?
Has he said anything yet?

410
00:29:24,128 --> 00:29:25,963
We are not having
this conversation.

411
00:29:25,997 --> 00:29:28,098
No. Of course not.

412
00:29:28,133 --> 00:29:30,300
No. I mean. We really
are not having it.

413
00:29:30,335 --> 00:29:34,038
You are asking me to violate
attorney-client privilege.

414
00:29:34,072 --> 00:29:35,339
Come on! Counselor.

415
00:29:35,472 --> 00:29:36,340
You know, I wish
people like you.

416
00:29:36,473 --> 00:29:37,442
Would stop saying: "Come on!
Counselor."

417
00:29:37,474 --> 00:29:39,344
I did not like it the first
time it happened today.

418
00:29:39,376 --> 00:29:41,179
A judge said it to me twice.

419
00:29:41,211 --> 00:29:43,213
And, more I hear it,
more I do not like it.

420
00:29:46,483 --> 00:29:49,086
Ok. Listen. I understand
attorney-client privilege.

421
00:29:49,119 --> 00:29:52,323
I understand all the
legal competitiveness.

422
00:29:52,356 --> 00:29:55,058
I understand that is
how you make a living.

423
00:29:55,093 --> 00:29:57,961
I am talking to you
about something else.

424
00:29:59,963 --> 00:30:02,066
The security of your country.

425
00:30:02,099 --> 00:30:05,236
And, I am sorry if the way
I put it offends you.

426
00:30:05,269 --> 00:30:08,940
We need to know. What
is Abel telling to you?

427
00:30:08,972 --> 00:30:11,041
Do you understand me, Donovan?

428
00:30:11,075 --> 00:30:13,111
We need to know.

429
00:30:13,144 --> 00:30:15,144
You do not go with
"Boy Scout" on me.

430
00:30:16,381 --> 00:30:18,381
We do not have a
rulebook, here.

431
00:30:19,384 --> 00:30:21,486
You are Agent Hoffman, yeah.

432
00:30:21,519 --> 00:30:23,387
Yeah.

433
00:30:23,421 --> 00:30:25,490
German extraction.

434
00:30:25,522 --> 00:30:26,958
Yeah, so?

435
00:30:26,990 --> 00:30:28,893
My name is Donovan. Irish.

436
00:30:28,926 --> 00:30:31,328
Both sides, mother and father.

437
00:30:31,362 --> 00:30:34,499
I am Irish. You are German.

438
00:30:34,531 --> 00:30:37,367
What makes us both Americans?

439
00:30:37,402 --> 00:30:39,470
Just one thing.

440
00:30:39,503 --> 00:30:41,503
One, one, one.

441
00:30:42,272 --> 00:30:44,272
The rulebook.

442
00:30:44,409 --> 00:30:46,176
We call it the Constitution.

443
00:30:46,211 --> 00:30:48,211
And, we agree to the rules.

444
00:30:48,413 --> 00:30:49,980
That is what makes
us Americans.

445
00:30:50,013 --> 00:30:51,148
It is all that makes
us Americans.

446
00:30:51,182 --> 00:30:52,250
So, do not tell me
there is no rulebook.

447
00:30:52,383 --> 00:30:54,885
And, do not nod at me like
that, you son of a bitch!

448
00:31:06,029 --> 00:31:08,029
Do we need to worry
about you?

449
00:31:09,067 --> 00:31:11,903
Not if I have been left
alone to do my job.

450
00:31:26,984 --> 00:31:28,219
From this moment, forward.

451
00:31:28,252 --> 00:31:30,989
You will not refer to the
U-2 as a spy plane.

452
00:31:31,021 --> 00:31:33,023
Or, reconnaissance aircraft.

453
00:31:33,057 --> 00:31:35,292
You will refer to it
as: "The Article."

454
00:31:35,326 --> 00:31:38,462
The Article has an
80-foot wingspan.

455
00:31:38,496 --> 00:31:44,001
A single Pratt powers and
Whitney J57 P-37 engine.

456
00:31:44,035 --> 00:31:46,403
10,000 pounds of thrust.

457
00:31:46,436 --> 00:31:50,474
A maximum speed of
430 miles an hour.

458
00:31:50,508 --> 00:31:52,242
She may not be quick,

459
00:31:52,277 --> 00:31:55,179
but at your cruising
altitude of 70,000 feet,

460
00:31:55,212 --> 00:31:57,015
nothing will come
close to you.

461
00:31:57,048 --> 00:31:58,182
70,000?

462
00:31:58,215 --> 00:32:01,184
The idea is the enemy does
not even, know you are there.

463
00:32:01,219 --> 00:32:03,219
It looks somewhat flimsy.

464
00:32:06,089 --> 00:32:10,094
Every extra pound of weight
costs a foot in altitude.

465
00:32:10,127 --> 00:32:12,127
We need to accommodate
the cameras.

466
00:32:14,097 --> 00:32:18,068
That is a 4,500-millimeter
lens, times three.

467
00:32:18,102 --> 00:32:20,404
A pin-sharp panoramic camera.

468
00:32:20,438 --> 00:32:25,076
Four times as powerful as any aerial
reconnaissance cameras we have ever used.

469
00:32:25,108 --> 00:32:28,313
You are going taking
pictures, many pictures.

470
00:32:28,346 --> 00:32:30,615
At 70,000 feet. The
Article can photograph.

471
00:32:30,647 --> 00:32:34,585
2,000 square miles of
territories in one pass.

472
00:32:34,618 --> 00:32:36,354
Now, drivers,

473
00:32:36,386 --> 00:32:39,523
give the Agent Sumner
your undivided attention.

474
00:32:39,557 --> 00:32:43,627
The items you will need on
your mission is all over here.

475
00:32:43,661 --> 00:32:46,364
<i>B camera, revere 8
model 40 magazine,</i>

476
00:32:46,396 --> 00:32:49,232
<i>Keystone Capri K-25, silver.</i>

477
00:32:49,267 --> 00:32:51,234
All how handle shaving brush.

478
00:32:51,269 --> 00:32:54,404
Complete set of cipher tablets
on edible silver, foil.

479
00:32:54,439 --> 00:32:56,439
Specialist photographic
equipment.

480
00:32:58,476 --> 00:33:01,179
Yeah. We get the idea.
Thank you.

481
00:33:13,357 --> 00:33:16,426
Excuse me. Agent Bosco.
"Blasco."

482
00:33:16,461 --> 00:33:18,296
<i>Sir.</i>

483
00:33:18,328 --> 00:33:23,334
There seems to be a
subsection to this list here.

484
00:33:23,367 --> 00:33:25,369
Most of this stuff
came from his studio.

485
00:33:25,403 --> 00:33:27,643
But, the rest is from the hotel
room he was holed up in.

486
00:33:27,672 --> 00:33:29,672
Where we found him.

487
00:33:30,540 --> 00:33:32,643
The hotel room you searched.

488
00:33:32,676 --> 00:33:34,444
Yeah.

489
00:33:34,479 --> 00:33:36,547
Can I see the warrant?

490
00:33:36,580 --> 00:33:38,580
What?

491
00:33:39,584 --> 00:33:42,153
Yeah, explain this to me.
There was a warrant.

492
00:33:42,185 --> 00:33:43,520
There was a warrant.

493
00:33:43,554 --> 00:33:45,623
A civil detention writ for
the arrest of an alien,

494
00:33:45,655 --> 00:33:47,525
but, there was no
search warrant,

495
00:33:47,557 --> 00:33:49,359
for suspicion of
criminal activity.

496
00:33:49,394 --> 00:33:50,627
So, the search,
and the evidence.

497
00:33:50,661 --> 00:33:52,396
That is the fruit
of that search,

498
00:33:52,430 --> 00:33:54,531
That is all tainted, and
should not be admitted.

499
00:33:54,565 --> 00:33:57,300
What protections he is due,
your honor. The man is not...

500
00:33:57,335 --> 00:34:00,171
Who is the man? He is
Rudolf Ivanovich Abel.

501
00:34:00,203 --> 00:34:02,105
He is a Soviet citizen.

502
00:34:02,140 --> 00:34:03,407
He is not an American.

503
00:34:03,441 --> 00:34:07,577
1886, Wick Wo vs. Hopkins.

504
00:34:07,612 --> 00:34:10,715
The court held that even aliens,
in case Chinese immigrants,

505
00:34:10,748 --> 00:34:14,117
